<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Male</emphasis>
(holotype). Body length 2.9 mm, mostly black (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Haltichella bomiana sp. nov. (holotype male) A habitus, lateral view B head, front view C antenna D head and part of mesosoma, dorsal view E forewing F propodeum G hind leg H metasoma I mesosoma, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1060.70427.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/588990" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">2A</figureCitation>
), head and mesosoma with dense punctures and white pubescence; antenna with scape yellowish brown and flagellum yellowish brown to brown; eye and ocelli silvery gray (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Haltichella bomiana sp. nov. (holotype male) A habitus, lateral view B head, front view C antenna D head and part of mesosoma, dorsal view E forewing F propodeum G hind leg H metasoma I mesosoma, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1060.70427.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/588990" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">2D</figureCitation>
); tegula yellowish brown; fore and mid legs yellowish brown; metacoxa black, metatrochanter yellowish brown, metafemur black with base yellowish brown to reddish brown, metatibia black with apex yellowish brown, metatarsus yellowish brown; fore wing largely hyaline with small brown patch adjoining marginal vein and venation brownish.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Head</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Haltichella bomiana sp. nov. (holotype male) A habitus, lateral view B head, front view C antenna D head and part of mesosoma, dorsal view E forewing F propodeum G hind leg H metasoma I mesosoma, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1060.70427.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/588990" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">2B, D</figureCitation>
) with coarsely rugose punctures, 1.2
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as wide as long in frontal view; scrobe slightly wider, not reaching anterior ocellus, finely striate; preorbital carinae distinct; POL 5
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as OOL; antenna (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Haltichella bomiana sp. nov. (holotype male) A habitus, lateral view B head, front view C antenna D head and part of mesosoma, dorsal view E forewing F propodeum G hind leg H metasoma I mesosoma, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1060.70427.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/588990" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">2C</figureCitation>
) slender; scape longer than pedicel to Fu2 combined; pedicel small; anellus short and transverse; Fu1 longest, 1.7
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as broad; Fu2-7 approximately equal in length, all the funicular segments longer than broad; club 2-segmented and slender, 3.2
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as maximum width, 2
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as and as broad as the preceding segment.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Mesosoma</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Haltichella bomiana sp. nov. (holotype male) A habitus, lateral view B head, front view C antenna D head and part of mesosoma, dorsal view E forewing F propodeum G hind leg H metasoma I mesosoma, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1060.70427.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/588990" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">2I</figureCitation>
) with dense punctures and white pubescence; apex of mesoscutellum with two diverging teeth, inner margins of the two teeth at a right angle; submedian carinae of propodeum (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Haltichella bomiana sp. nov. (holotype male) A habitus, lateral view B head, front view C antenna D head and part of mesosoma, dorsal view E forewing F propodeum G hind leg H metasoma I mesosoma, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1060.70427.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/588990" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">2F</figureCitation>
) indicated, distinct on posterior half. Fore wing hyaline (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Haltichella bomiana sp. nov. (holotype male) A habitus, lateral view B head, front view C antenna D head and part of mesosoma, dorsal view E forewing F propodeum G hind leg H metasoma I mesosoma, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1060.70427.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/588990" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">2E</figureCitation>
), forewing 2.6
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as broad; submarginal vein 4
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as marginal vein, marginal vein 1.6
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as postmarginal vein, postmarginal vein slightly longer than stigmal vein. Metafemur and metatibia with long and white pubescence (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Haltichella bomiana sp. nov. (holotype male) A habitus, lateral view B head, front view C antenna D head and part of mesosoma, dorsal view E forewing F propodeum G hind leg H metasoma I mesosoma, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1060.70427.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/588990" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">2G</figureCitation>
); metacoxa with coxal tooth on baso-dorsal side; metafemur 2.3
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as broad, with a row of comb of teeth.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Metasoma</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Haltichella bomiana sp. nov. (holotype male) A habitus, lateral view B head, front view C antenna D head and part of mesosoma, dorsal view E forewing F propodeum G hind leg H metasoma I mesosoma, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1060.70427.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/588990" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">2H</figureCitation>
) fusiform, 2
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as broad in dorsal view; Gt1 dorsum smooth and shiny, occupying 0.6
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
length of metasoma, with two longitudinal carinae at base; Gt2 with basal half smooth and distal half with microsculptured and white pubescence; dorsal surface of Gt2-6 with sparse microsculptured and white pubescence.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Female.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
